INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('114', '1', '2017-01-23 13:52:10', '2017-01-23 13:52:10', 'Even Michelangelo got paid for doing the Sistine Chapel. To those artists who say they’re doing it for the love of art, I say: Get real. It pains me physically to see a woman victimized, rendered pathetic, by fashion. I don’t like trends. They tend to make everybody look the same. It’s sometimes said that I’m rebellious and I do things to push people’s buttons, but I just like the challenge. We look our best in subdued colors, sophisticated cuts, and a general air of sleek understatement.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nAttention to detail is of utmost importance when you want to look good. I never like to think that I design for a particular person. I design for the woman I wanted to be, the woman I used to be, and – to some degree – the woman I’m still a little piece of. Design and style should work toward making you look good and feel good without a lot of effort so you can get on with the things that matter. I am not interested in the past, except as the road to the future. I am always locked in my design studio.\r\n\r\nDesign and style should work toward making you look good and feel good without a lot of effort so you can get on with the things that matter. The great thing about fashion is that it always looks forward. Nostalgia is a very complicated subject for me. I’m attracted by nostalgia but I refuse it intellectually. What I hate is nasty, ugly people. I didn’t want to be a fashion designer, and for a good half of my career I didn’t like it. I always wanted to do other things.\r\n\r\nFashion fosters cliches of beauty, but I want to tear them apart. It’s useless to send models out on the runway to cry. Today, I’m very happy about myself, because I realized my dreams. I learned how to understand what people want. My breakfast is very important. I am never satisfied with myself and that is what keeps me going – I have no post-satisfaction.\r\n\r\nI have an obsession with details and pattern. I’m a fashion designer and people think, what do I know? Those fashion designers are just crazy; but aren’t we all? Fashion never stops. There is always the new project, the new opportunity. Fashion is to please your eye. Shapes and proportions are for your intellect.', 'Design and style should work!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'design-and-style-should-work', '', '', '2017-01-23 13:52:10', '2017-01-23 13:52:10', '', '0', 'http://lojavirtual.vialoja.com.br/?p=114', '0', 'post', '', '0');
